I am writing this statement to formally plead guilty to the charge of being drunk and disorderly. I understand the seriousness of my actions and the impact they had on others. I would like to take this opportunity to express my deep remorse and regret for my behavior.

My name is Paul Nicholls, and I am 54 years old. I have always strived to be a law-abiding citizen, and this incident is completely out of character for me. I want to assure the court that I do not have a history of such behavior. In fact, the only previous conviction on my record is from 10 years ago for careless driving, which I deeply regret as well.

I understand that my actions were unacceptable and that I failed to exercise self-control in that situation. I deeply apologize to anyone who was affected by my behavior, and I take full responsibility for my actions.

In light of this incident, I am committed to taking the necessary steps to ensure that such behavior does not occur again. I am dedicated to engaging in whatever measures the court deems appropriate to rectify this situation. I am open and willing to comply with any directives, including counseling or alternative methods, to address the issue at hand.

Once again, I would like to express my profound regret for my behavior. I am truly sorry for any harm or inconvenience I may have caused, and I hope that the court can see the genuine remorse I feel.

Thank you for your attention to this matter.

Respectfully,
Paul Nicholls

